content.text: When mathematical symbols "0" and "1" are physically arranged on paper: - Horizontal touching: Observed as "01" - Vertical touching: Observed as "10" - Separated arrangement: Observed as "0∠1" - Critical distance: May produce AlienatedNumber("01") or collapse to singularity Ø This simple observation reveals that mathematical identity is inseparable from spatial configuration, fundamentally challenging the abstraction principle of traditional mathematics
